dct_description_sm: Compiled and drawn in the Cartographic Section of the National Geographic Society. James M. Darley, chief cartographer.
Shows all of Africa north of the Equator.
Issued with the National geographic magazine, v. 106, no. 6, Dec. 1954.
Insets (a, b, and d, scale 1:2,500,000) : a. Eastern Mediterranean, Dead Sea to Damascus.--b. Eastern Mediterranean, Damascus to Antioch.--c. The Great Rift Valley.--d. Nile Delta and the Suez Canal.
